"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkLatticeOpRuleCached</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">rhs</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">op</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp\">LatticeOp</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Context.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGenM\">VCGenM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Apply.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.BackwardRule\">Meta.Sym.BackwardRule</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Cached construction of a lattice-split backward rule for the operator heading `rhs`. On a cache miss\nthe rewrite and terminal sets are assembled from the built-in seeds and the operator's `@[frameproc]`\ncontributions (`fp?`); a cache hit skips that work.\n\nCache key: the `head … cₙ` prefix built from the constant arguments (which the rule bakes in verbatim)\nand the argument count (which fixes the schematic operand and state count).\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/RuleCache.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.mkLatticeOpRuleCached","kind":"def","line":69,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.mkLatticeOpRuleCached","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/RuleCache.lean#L69-L83"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/RuleCache.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.mkBackwardRuleForSplitCached\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span 